You could give each of your buttons a class, and add a click event listener to elements with that class. When the button is clicked, you can get its id number using `this.id.match(/\d+/g);`, and use then use the number retrieved in your other selectors:

    $(&quot;.myClass&quot;).click(function() {
      const [n] = this.id.match(/\d+/g); // get number from the id
      $(&quot;#q&quot;+n).hide();
      $(&quot;#q&quot;+(+n+1)).show();
